---
title: Pan Fried Chicken Thigh, Roasted Butternut, Quinoa and Halloumi Salad with Tahini Dressing
description: Food fact! Quinoa is so nutritious and protein-packed that NASA has recommended it for space flights and the United Nations has suggested it for feeding people in areas where food is scarce. Not only is it good for us, but quinoa also has a wonderful nutty taste that works great in a salad, particularly with the sweet and salty flavour of butternut with halloumi. When all the ingredients are cooked, drizzle the dish with tahini dressing and sprinkle with walnuts for a heavenly dinnertime experience.
